 MBOMBELA –According to police spokesman Capt Zandile Gqawa, the incidents were more prevelant in the central business district (CBD). The most affected areas are Henshall Street, Brown Street, Anderson Street, Bester Street, Samora Machel Drive and Ferreira Street. “There are incidents in parking areas and in some shopping complexes and malls.” She said the community is requested not to leave valuable items such as laptops, cameras, cellphones, clothes etc on the seats or where criminals can easily gain access. “They are also requested to always ensure that all vehicle doors and windows are properly locked before moving away from the vehicle. They are requested to lock the vehicle doors and windows when approaching stop signs and traffic lights.” She concluded that the public must report any suspicious activities to the police.